### API Collection - Sistema de Admisión de Postgrado FIIS UNI
### Base URL Configuration
@baseUrl = http://postgrado-fiis.test
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api

### Authentication Variables
@token = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
@applicantId = YOUR_APPLICANT_ID_HERE
@programUuid = YOUR_PROGRAM_UUID_HERE

---

## ============================================
## 📚 PROGRAMAS (Programs)
## ============================================

### GET - Obtener todos los programas
GET {{apiUrl}}/admission/programs
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

###

### GET - Obtener un programa por UUID
GET {{apiUrl}}/admission/program/{{programUuid}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

###

### GET - Obtener documentos requeridos de un programa
GET {{apiUrl}}/admission/program/{{programUuid}}/documents
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

---

## ============================================
## 🔐 AUTENTICACIÓN (Authentication)
## ============================================

### POST - Login
POST {{apiUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "usuario@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### ⬆️ Response:
# {
#   "status": "success",
#   "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
#   "user": {
#     "id": 1,
#     "name": "Juan Pérez",
#     "email": "usuario@example.com",
#     "roles": [
#       {
#         "id": 1,
#         "name": "postulante",
#         "guard_name": "api"
#       }
#     ]
#   },
#   "role": ["postulante"],
#   "message": "Login exitoso"
# }

###

### GET - Obtener usuario actual (Requiere token)
GET {{apiUrl}}/auth/user
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### POST - Logout (Requiere token)
POST {{apiUrl}}/logout
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### ⚠️ NOTA SOBRE AUTENTICACIÓN
# Para cualquier endpoint protegido, debe incluir el header:
# Authorization: Bearer <tu_token_aqui>
#
# El token se obtiene del response del login y debe ser persistido
# en la sesión de NextAuth para usar en requests posteriores.
#
# En componentes de React:
# const { data: session } = useSession();
# const token = session?.accessToken;

---

## ============================================
## 👤 POSTULANTES (Applicants)
## ============================================

### POST - Registrar nuevo postulante
POST {{apiUrl}}/applicant/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Juan",
  "last_name": "Pérez",
  "email": "juan.perez@example.com",
  "phone": "+51987654321",
  "program_uuid": "{{programUuid}}"
}

###

### GET - Obtener datos del postulante
GET {{apiUrl}}/applicant/{{applicantId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### PUT - Actualizar datos del postulante
PUT {{apiUrl}}/applicant/{{applicantId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "first_name": "Juan",
  "last_name": "Pérez García",
  "phone": "+51987654321"
}

###

### POST - Subir documentos del postulante
POST {{apiUrl}}/applicant/{{applicantId}}/documents
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="document_type_id"

1
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="document"; filename="documento.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./public/sample.pdf
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

###

---

## ============================================
## 📄 DOCUMENTOS (Documents)
## ============================================

### GET - Obtener tipos de documentos
GET {{apiUrl}}/document-types
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

###

### GET - Obtener documentos del postulante
GET {{apiUrl}}/applicant/{{applicantId}}/documents
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### GET - Descargar documento (usando full_url)
GET {{baseUrl}}/storage/documents/filename.pdf
Accept: application/pdf

---

## ============================================
## 🎤 ENTREVISTAS (Interviews)
## ============================================

### GET - Obtener disponibilidades de entrevistas
GET {{apiUrl}}/interview/availabilities
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

###

### GET - Obtener citas de entrevista del postulante
GET {{apiUrl}}/interview/appointments
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### POST - Programar entrevista
POST {{apiUrl}}/interview/appointments
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "interview_availability_id": 1,
  "applicant_id": "{{applicantId}}"
}

###

### PUT - Actualizar cita de entrevista
PUT {{apiUrl}}/interview/appointments/{{appointmentId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "interview_availability_id": 2
}

###

### DELETE - Cancelar cita de entrevista
DELETE {{apiUrl}}/interview/appointments/{{appointmentId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

---

## ============================================
## 🏫 PERIODOS ACADÉMICOS (Academic Periods)
## ============================================

### GET - Obtener periodos académicos
GET {{apiUrl}}/academic-periods
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

###

### GET - Obtener periodo académico activo
GET {{apiUrl}}/academic-periods/active
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

---

## ============================================
## 🏦 BANCOS (Banks)
## ============================================

### GET - Obtener lista de bancos
GET {{apiUrl}}/banks
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

---

## ============================================
## 🏫 UNIVERSIDAD (University)
## ============================================

### GET - Obtener información de la universidad
GET {{apiUrl}}/university
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

###

### GET - Obtener facultades
GET {{apiUrl}}/university/faculties
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

---

## ============================================
## 📋 SOLICITUDES (Applications)
## ============================================

### GET - Obtener solicitud del postulante
GET {{apiUrl}}/application/{{applicantId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### GET - Obtener estado de solicitud
GET {{apiUrl}}/application/{{applicantId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

---

## ============================================
## 💡 NOTAS Y REFERENCIAS
## ============================================

# Variables de entorno necesarias:
# NEXT_BACKEND_API_URL=http://postgrado-fiis.test
# NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
# NEXTAUTH_SECRET=tu_secret_aqui

# Instrucciones de uso en WebStorm/IntelliJ:
# 1. Abre este archivo (api.http)
# 2. Reemplaza las variables en @<variable>
# 3. Haz clic en "Send Request" (botón verde) en cada endpoint
# 4. Ver respuestas en el panel de abajo

# Headers comunes:
# - Content-Type: application/json (para JSON)
# - Authorization: Bearer <token> (para endpoints protegidos)
# - Accept: application/json (para especificar formato esperado)

# Códigos de respuesta esperados:
# 200 - OK
# 201 - Created
# 204 - No Content
# 400 - Bad Request
# 401 - Unauthorized
# 403 - Forbidden
# 404 - Not Found
# 422 - Unprocessable Entity
# 500 - Internal Server Error

# Ejemplo de token (reemplazar con token real):
# eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# Para más información, consultar context.md en la raíz del proyecto

